The duties and responsibilities of the clerk shall include but not be limited to the following:
Maintenance and safekeeping of the permanent records of the city;
Performance of the duties required of the "official custodian" or "custodian" in accordance with KRS 61.870 to 61.882;
Possession of the seal of the city if used;
No later than January 31 of each year, mail to the Department for Local Government a list containing current city information including but not limited to the following:
The correct name of the mayor, legislative body members, and the following appointed officials who are serving as of January 1 of each year:
City clerk;
City treasurer;
City manager;
City attorney;
Finance director;
Police chief;
Fire chief; and
Public works director;
The correct name of the city, mailing address for city hall, and telephone number of city hall; and
The name and telephone number of either an elected or appointed official to serve as a contact person that may be reached during normal business hours of 8 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.;
Performance of all other duties and responsibilities required of the city clerk by statute or ordinance; and
The Department for Local Government shall immediately forward one (1) copy of the information received from each city clerk to the Legislative Research Commission.
